"Maybe I bought a bit too much... It was really heavy. Powdered things are pretty heavy..."

I also bought some beautiful toys and a few accessories that I thought would look good on Konomi.

If we plan on returning Konomi to the elf village, there isn't much time until the full moon.

I wanted to do everything I could until then, and the result was this huge load.

Financially, I may have been a bit overspending. I don't have much of a salary, but I've been spending way too much.

I don't mind pushing myself a little as long as it makes Konomi happy.

I think we'll be able to manage until the full moon.

Even if Konomi forgets, I want her to enjoy this moment.

However, lately I've been busy flirting with Konomi so I don't have much to sell.

I know I should be making crafts and preserving foods, but when Konomi keeps bothering me I end up putting off a lot of work.

Also, it's hard to say that the exploration of the surrounding area has progressed very well, since all I have time for is cuddling Konomi.

Although he sometimes speaks arrogant things to Konomi, when he thinks about the limited time until the full moon, he ends up wanting to spend as much time with her as possible.

When Konomi returns to the elf village, she'll have to work hard and do lots of things.

Just the village is not enough, so I'll have to think a bit about going to town.

Even though we had limited time, the thought of being separated from Konomi made it hard to believe.

